2 nam etc.] S. has just said magistrates nowadays are not sase or honoured because of their position. Now he gives the proofs. Is they use force, that is tyranny, and the natural end will be a tyrant’s fate— even is their aims are good. If they don't use force, and keep to eon- stitutional means they will find themselves powerless and only get unpopular: only a fool would do this (and a fool is not honoured: see on ἓ 3)-
